*HPC Software Analyst (100% remote)*

Work Description
The High Performance Computing (HPC) Software Analyst furthers the research goals of our scientists by installing, testing, and maintaining used by researchers in ExxonMobil Research & Engineering.

Specifics tasks & responsibilities
Position is responsible for obtaining, compiling/building, installing and troubleshooting software for all users of the HPC cluster. The user community uses a wide variety of software, including open source and vendor software running on both Linux and Windows across many different programming languages. Software is often parallelized and must work with HPC compute resource scheduler. Additionally, analysts interface with other EMIT teams to meet compliance and licensing requirements for software usage in ExxonMobil. While our HPC systems support a research-driven community we provide a production level of service.
Nice to have: previous experience in HPC technologies, preferably InfiniBand and Slurm.

Primary Skills Required
· 1 year of Linux command line experience
o Bash, modulefiles
· Experience installing C++ and Python software from source code in Linux environment
· Understanding of concepts related to parallel computing
o MPI Standard, multi-processing
· Ability to troubleshoot performance related issues when running software
· Experiencing with scripting and automation to reproduce software builds
